The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, August 08, 2004 				 Bus union seeks fare hike
																								Calcutta, Aug. 7: The Bengal Bus Syndicate has demanded that fares in the Calcutta metropolitan area be raised after the recent hike in oil prices.																								It has proposed that the minimum fare in Calcutta, Howrah, Hooghly and parts of South and North 24-Parganas be raised from Rs 3 to Rs 3.60. 																								At an emergency meeting today, the syndicate decided to submit a memorandum to transport minister Subhas Chakraborty demanding an immediate fare increase. 
